        <svcproc svcproctype="check" graphiccount="0">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Prior to performing this service procedure, it is necessary to determine if the vehicle has
                        the old or new type expansion valve (Table 1). The old or new expansion valve can be identified
                        by the vendor part number stamped on the valve. The part number can be determined with the
                        expansion valve in the vehicle.
                    </para>
                </note>
                <note>
                    <para>This procedure should be performed when installing a new improved expansion valve for the
                        first time in a vehicle built according to the dates listed above.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Replace the expansion valve with the new valve following the procedures in service
                    section CTS-5255.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate the power distribution panel.</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">9000 Model: located behind the glove box door on the passenger side of dash.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">9800 Model: located behind the engine cover.</para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Replace air conditioning relay (R6) with part number 2503522C1.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>To aid identification, the new relay, part number 2503522C1, has a green color case.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Operate the air conditioning system to verify correct operation.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="3">
            <title>Alternate Service Procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>This procedure should only be used if air conditioning relay (R6) is NOT being replaced with
                        part number 2503522C1.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Replace the expansion valve with the new valve following the procedures in service
                    section CTS-5255.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Batteries expel gases. Keep sparks, flames, burning cigarettes, or other ignition sources away
                        at all times. Always wear safety glasses and a face shield when working near batteries to
                        prevent personal injury.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect positive battery cable at the battery.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate the power distribution panel.</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">9000 Models: open the glove box on the passenger side of the dash and disable the
                        door stops so it will open fully.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">9800 Models: the power distribution panel is located behind the engine cover.</para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove all lower relays R1 through R12.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove mounting screws to allow the power distribution panel to be moved for clearance.
                    There is one screw at each lower mounting leg and one screw at the upper left side mounting support
                    rod
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9916021">(Figure 1)</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f9916021" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9916021.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Power Distribution Panel</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the retaining screws that secure the inter-latching relay connectors to the power
                    distribution panel
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9916021">(Figure 1)</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the connector body for air conditioning relay (R6).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Pull the white lock tab out from the electrical harness connector.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use a plug lock tool to release the terminals for wires 77R/77D and 77D in R6 relay
                    connector cavities 4 and 5
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9916022">(Figure 2)</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f9916022" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9916022.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. Release Wires 77R/77D and 77D</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Clip the jumper wire 77D at the terminal end on 77R.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <caution>
                        <para>Do not clip the terminal off wire 77R.</para>
                    </caution>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the terminal end on wire 77R into R6 relay connector cavity 5
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9916023">(Figure 3)</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f9916023" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9916023.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 3. Install Terminal End on Wire 77R</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-assemble the power distribution panel following the previous steps in reverse
                    order.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Operate the air conditioning system to verify correct operation.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
